<!-- Deleted image removed: [[Image:nurp.gif|right]] -->The '''National Undersea Research Center for the North Atlantic and Great Lakes''' (NURC-NA&GL) is one of six undersea centers established by the [[National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration]]'s [[National Undersea Research Program|Undersea Research Program]]. It is co-located with the [[University of Connecticut]]’s Department of Marine Sciences. The center's mission includes supporting regional and national [[oceanography]] research and promoting awareness of the oceanic ecosystem through educational outreach programs. 

